summary: On the 1st day of Christmas... So this is me using the 12 days of Christmas (which do indeed start on Christmas Day, not in...
caption:
On the 1st day of Christmas…

So this is me using the 12 days of Christmas (which do indeed start on Christmas Day, not in Advent #OffMySoapBox), to reminisce about 12 memorable Christmas pressies I received down the years, and I’m guessing this baby needs no introduction.

As with so many geeks of my generation, for me the Millennium Falcon was quite simply the must-have present for Christmas. The play-value was immense (other than the difficulty in lowering two of the landing legs), and the smuggling compartment was a particular joy to hide figures in.

Yes, you could only fit two figures in the cockpit (& that was a squeeze), yes, it only had one laser turret, with the underside one missing, plus the figures adopted a bizarre upside-down position to use it, and yes, the ramp broke so very easily. But despite those limitations, it was an absolute joy to own, and easily my favourite Star Wars spaceship from the range.

My only regret was removing the cardboard walls inside, because I gullibly believed my ‘mate’ when he said further rooms lurked behind it.

title: שובר קופות - חמישה סרטים שהפתיעו לטובה וחמישה לרעה ב-2018
body:

מהם הסרטים שעשו לנו את 2018 ואילו סרטים כמעט הרסו לנו את השנה? בואו נראה.

שנת 2018 הגיעה לסופה והחלטתי להעיף מבט על סרטים שהפתיעו אותי לטובה וסרטים שהפתיעו אותי לרעה השנה. יכול להיות שלא תסכימו איתי על חלקם ואשמח לשמוע את דעתכם בעניין, אבל אלו הסרטים שהפתיעו אותי לרעה או לטובה לפי הציפיות שהיו כלפיהם כשהם יצאו למסך הגדול.

title: The Mandalorian Composer
body:
The Mandalorian series will be composed by Ludwig Goransson. He previously worked on Black Panther, both Creed movies and Venom. It is great that they were able to get him to come onto the show because based on his past works he is amazing.

He said, “Words fail to express how surreal and humbling it feels to be invited into the Star Wars universe, In these next months I hope to honor the tradition of Star Wars’ musical landscape while propelling The Mandalorian into new and uncharted territory, And I will try to remember that there is no try.“

https://www.cnet.com/news/star-wars-the-mandalorian-to-score-black-panther-composer-ludwig-goransson/

He said, “Words fail to express how surreal and humbling it feels to be invited into the Star Wars universe, In these next months I hope to honor the tradition of Star Wars’ musical landscape while propelling The Mandalorian into new and uncharted territory, And I will try to remember that there is no try.“
